      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this contract for a freelance gig and i don't really get what \"indemnification\" means. can u explain it in plain english?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in plain English, is basically a promise where one party agrees to cover the costs or losses of another party if a specific bad thing happens. Think of it like this: if you promise to cover the costs if a certain type of trouble comes your way, you're indemnifying them. It's a way of shifting the risk, making sure one party doesn't end up holding the bag for something the other party caused.",
