    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. but the clause i'm looking at says i have to indemnify them against \"any and all third-party claims of infringement.\" that sounds pretty scary... like i could get sued by someone i don't even know because of a design i made. what kind of things would actually trigger that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This part is a very common, albeit potentially worrying, clause. It means you are agreeing to step in and pay for any legal trouble—like lawsuits or damages—that a third party brings against them because of something you did, specifically related to copyright, patent, or trademark infringement. It's a way of saying, \"If my work somehow messes up someone else's intellectual property, I'll cover the resulting legal bill.\" You'd be indemnifying them against things like someone suing them because your design accidentally copied a logo they own.",
      "source": "target",
