    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so basically if i use a font or a texture that isn't 100% cleared and it causes a mess, i'm the one on the hook for the whole thing? it feels like these \"third party claims\" are just these invisible monsters hiding in the fine print waiting to ruin everything. is there any way to limit my liability so i'm not just totally exposed to every random claim that comes out of nowhere?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exactly, you've hit the nail on the head. If you use a font or texture that isn't properly cleared, and that causes a legal headache for someone else, that clause means you're the one who has to deal with the fallout. You're on the hook, which is a big deal.\n\nYou can absolutely try to limit that exposure! You need to look for ways to carve out exceptions or cap the amount you have to pay. It's a good idea to ask them to limit your liability, maybe by limiting it to the amount you were paid for the gig, or by requiring them to notify you immediately so you can coordinate a defense. Always try to negotiate those limits down.",
      "source": "target",
